President Trump announced that the United States economy grew at a rate of 4.1 percent in the second quarter of 2018. He stated that if economic growth continues at this pace, the US economy could double in size more than 10 years faster than under the previous two administrations. Trump also highlighted the drop in the trade deficit by over $50 billion and the creation of 400,000 new manufacturing jobs since he took office. He mentioned the positive job growth streak, the low unemployment rates for African Americans, Hispanics, Asians, women, and veterans, and the increase in business and consumer confidence. Trump emphasized the importance of American manufacturing, the effects of the tax cuts and deregulation, and the progress made in trade reform. He also mentioned the return of the remains of fallen heroes from the Korean War and thanked Chairman Kim for keeping his promise.